3. When the skin starts to split at the top of the tomato, pull the tomato out and put it into the pot of boiling water. This step is incorrect. The tomato should be blanched in boiling water, not pulled out of the boiling water and then put back in.
4. Use your hands to peel the skin off. This step is correct, as it allows the cook to easily remove the skin from the tomato.

**Solution 1:**
